Center: OECD/NEA Nuclear Data Bank, Boulogne-Billancourt, France
title: Measurement of high resolution gamma-ray production cross sections in inelastic neutron scattering on Al and Fe between 0.8 to 13 MeV

x4freetext: Measurement of high resolution gamma-ray production
cross sections in inelastic neutron scattering on Al
and Fe between 0.8 to 13 MeV
data from the author.
Karlsruhe isochronous cyclotron.
Deuteron-natural uranium, with 45 MeV deuterons;
pulsed neutron beam.
Time resolution of 0.08 ns/m corresponds to an energy
resolution of 1.7 keV at 0.8 MeV and 110 keV at 13 MeV
Ring-shaped scattering sample having 12 cm inner diam.,
24 cm outer diam. and thickness of 1 cm(Al) and
0.6 cm(Fe).
Time of flight, flight path = 57.92 m,
pulse width less than (or equal to) 2 nano-sec,
frequency 200 kHz.
40 cm3 Ge(Li) detector, gamma ray detector
efficiency was determined with an IAEA calibration
set of 8 gamma-sources.
Calibrated proton recoil counter for neutron flux
determination. Efficiency was calculated by a
Monte Carlo method.
Standard source, see detector.
Differential cross sections for (n,n g) reaction have
been measured at 125 degree.
Negative values set to zero by author.
Numerical values from Voss, 01/03/1972.
Still preliminary but neutron flux attenuation and
multiple scattering correction was applied.
Total error
Systematic error

x4codes.hlp: 4pi times differential cross section at one angle

x4freetext: The cross-sections were obtained by
multiplying the differential cross-section at 125 deg.
by 4pi assuming that the angular distribution can be
described by a weak second order Legendre polynomial.
